climbs.name: Hydrogen Psychosis
climbs.fa: Matt Scherer, Jacob Mader: Ground Up

content.description: Aid or free climb up the crack on the right then nail and hook your way to the left leaning seam. nail and place bodyweight pro to the top of the seam then make hook moves getting out of the seam followed buy some easier free moves.
content.protection: 000 C3-2# C4, knifeblades, beaks, soft metal, hooks, rp's, micro nuts
content.location: park at the black elk peak trail head and walk towards litte devils tower trail head. look for an obvious left leaning seam with a fixed pin on the left side of the trial.

content.description: The Submarine is a very obvious chunk of rock when leaving the parking lot of Sylvan Lake Day Use. Look for the small formation right before the old mining tunnel. Look for the obvious Seam/ crack that splits the face that is facing the trail. There is two known routes one is a top rope and one that was recently put up on lead. Any other information let me know and i can change.
